A quick solution is to use [Yarn resolutions](https://yarnpkg.com/lang/en/docs/selective-version-resolutions/) which should force correct new version. Note that it is only supported in Yarn (not NPM) and it will still produce error output (but it won't fail installation).

You need to add this to `package.json`:

```json
{
  "resolutions": {
    "eth-lib/keccakjs/sha3": "^1.2.3",
    "web3/web3-eth/web3-eth-accounts/scrypt.js": "^0.3.0"
  }
}
```
